OL,7,FThe IMF is rarely explicitly critical
OL,8,Fof wealthy advanced economies and is
OL,9,Foften useful ally.
OL,11,FIn 2010, the Cameron-Clegg coalition
OL,12,Fgovernment pursued its programme of
OL,13,Fausterity (spending cuts and tax
OL,14,Frises) with the IMF's public backing,
OL,15,Finitially at least.
OL,17,FIn September 2022, the IMF warned Liz
OL,18,FTruss's government that her proposals
OL,19,Ffor unfunded tax cuts were ill-advised
OL,20,Fand risked pushing up prices and
OL,21,Ffuelling inflation.
