OL,4,Cbrands Hunt's spending plans
OL,5,Cunrealistic
OL,7,FResponding to the IMF's comments, Mr
OL,8,FHunt said: "The IMF expect growth to
OL,9,Fstrengthen over the next few years,
OL,10,Fsupported by our introduction of the
OL,11,Fbiggest capital investment tax reliefs
OL,12,Fanywhere in the world, alongside
OL,13,FNational Insurance cuts to improve
OL,14,Fwork incentives.
OL,16,F"It is too early to know whether
OL,17,Ffurther reductions in tax will be
OL,18,Faffordable in the Budget, but we
OL,19,Fcontinue to believe that smart tax
OL,20,Freductions can make a big difference
OL,21,Fin boosting growth."
